  "texts": [
    "To the best of our knowledge, MAiVAR is the first audio-image to video fusion-based action classification framework that uses image-based representations of audio to leverage CNN architecture for better action recognition.",
    "The key contributions of our work can be summarized as follows:• We introduce MAiVAR, and a new multi-staged multimodal framework that supports novel dominant head audio-visual fusion.",
    "Our fusion approach eliminates expensive fusion operations, significantly reducing the computational complexity of the model.",
    "Our framework can be applied to different tasks with minimal changes to the overall architecture.",
    "• We build a new feature representation strategy to select the most informative candidate representations for audio-visual fusion."
  ],
